title._content: Sunrise over the Burdick Elevator at New Ulm, Minnesota...

description._content: Original Caption: Sunrise over the Burdick Elevator at New Ulm, Minnesota. It Was Built on the Site of the Eagle Roller Mill Which Was the Town's Largest Industry until the 1940's. The Town Was Founded in 1854 by a Group of German Immigrants. The County Seat Trading Center Remains Predominately a Farming Community Although Its Growth Since 1950 Has Been Due to the Arrival of Manufacturing Businesses the Business District Has Been Revitalized as a Community Project.
